    <h2>⚠️ Why Regex Email Validation Is Fundamentally Limited <span class="badge">RFC 5321 / 5322</span></h2>

    <!-- RFC callout -->
    <div class="rfc-callout">
      <strong>RFC 5321</strong> (SMTP) and <strong>RFC 5322</strong> (Internet Message Format) define the actual
      rules for valid email addresses. These specifications are so complex that a fully compliant
      regex would be thousands of characters long — and still wouldn't be able to verify whether
      an address actually <em>exists</em>.
    </div>

    <hr class="divider" />

    <!-- Limitations -->
