## What's Inside

### 🔍 Live Validator Card
| Feature | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Real-time feedback** | Fires on every `input` event |
| **Green border** | CSS class `.valid` applied when regex passes |
| **Red border** | CSS class `.invalid` applied when regex fails |
| **Status icon** | ✅ / ❌ appears inside the input field |
| **Diagnostic messages** | Specific reason *why* it failed (no `@`, bad TLD, etc.) |
| **Regex display** | The exact pattern is printed on screen |
| **Clickable test cases** | 10 samples (valid & invalid) you can click to auto-fill |

### ⚠️ Limitations Section
Explains **7 concrete reasons** why regex cannot fully validate emails: RFC complexity, comments, quoted local parts, Unicode/IDN, new TLDs, existence, and context-free grammar theory.

### ✅ Alternatives Section
Five production-ready strategies ranked by approach: double opt-in, browser native validation, DNS/MX lookup, RFC-compliant libraries, and third-party verification APIs.

