## The Sensible Production Strategy

```
1. LOOSE SYNTAX CHECK    →  /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/
                             Just catch obvious garbage. Nothing more.

2. TYPO SUGGESTION       →  mailcheck.js
                             "Did you mean gmail.com?"

3. MX RECORD CHECK       →  dns.resolveMx() server-side
                             Does this domain accept email at all?

4. SEND CONFIRMATION     →  The only real validation.
                             Require a click before trusting the address.

5. MONITOR BOUNCES       →  Track hard bounces in production.
                             Remove them. Maintain list hygiene.
```

The regex is step one of five, and it is the least important step. Any developer who stops at the regex and calls it "validated" has validated nothing.

